ole=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5826844\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5826844\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104agc1705663492838.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/agc1705663492838.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/agc1705663492838.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bkp1665702824339\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Working with Language Setups\n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Language setups allow you to deploy a Uniface application in different languages.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13679e1_d13680e1_d13681e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__p_d26930e1_d26931e1_d26932e1\">Load source definitions for standard language\n               setups from <span class=\"ph filepath\">libmsg.usys.xml</span>, located in the\n                  <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface\\misc</span> directory of your installation. Create a\n               Library. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Import the <span class=\"ph filepath\">libmsg.usys.xml</span>:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__p_d26933e1_d26934e1_d26935e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">/cpy\n                     d:Uniface\\uniface\\misc\\libmsg.usys.xml</code>\n</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13682e1_d13683e1_d13684e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the language setups.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13685e1_d13686e1_d13687e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you want to define your own language setups, first create a new library or\n                     use one you already created for global objects. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cqe1665702873537.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cqe1665702873537.html\" title=\"A language setup is a collection of definitions that specify the texts and formatting of language-related data that may be visible in the user interface of a desktop application.\">Language Setups</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13688e1_d13689e1_d13690e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span> and then select the one of the language setups:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13691e1_d13692e1_d13693e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Date-time properties</span>—date and time formats.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13694e1_d13695e1_d13696e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Editor messages</span>—Uniface text editor messages\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13697e1_d13698e1_d13699e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Button Text</span>—button text in panels, as well as texts for structure editor functions such as Next Occurrence\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13700e1_d13701e1_d13702e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle Symbols</span>—labels for the Character Attributes menu, and check boxes in panels\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13703e1_d13704e1_d13705e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Japanese Eras</span>—Japanese eras based on the reigns of the emperors\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13706e1_d13707e1_d13708e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select or create the library to contain the language definitions. For more\n                     information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ita1705565048634.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ita1705565048634.html\" title=\"To create libraries of modeled properties, global objects, and language setups, use the editors available in the More Editors menu.\">Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects</a>. </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13709e1_d13710e1_d13711e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__p_d26936e1_d26937e1_d26938e1\">Select an existing definition or define a\n                     new one. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">For example, to create a French language definition, enter\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">FRA</code>as the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Name</span> and click\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>. </div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13712e1_d13713e1_d13714e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__p_d26939e1_d26940e1_d26941e1\">In the resulting dialog, set the properties\n                     of the type of language setup.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">For help on specific properties, press <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">F1</span>.</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13715e1_d13716e1_d13717e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__p_d26942e1_d26943e1_d26944e1\">Apply a language definition by setting the\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$language</span> ProcScript function or the\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$LANGUAGE</span> assignment setting to the desired language. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$language</span> in ProcScript overrides the\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$LANGUAGE</span> assignment setting.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__p_d26945e1_d26946e1_d26947e1\">Setting the application language affects not\n                  only the language setups, but also global objects such as menus, glyphs, messages,\n                  and help texts.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13718e1_d13719e1_d13720e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Distribute a language setup:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13721e1_d13722e1_d13723e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Export the language setup using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/lse</span> command line\n                     switch.</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13724e1_d13725e1_d13726e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__p_d26948e1_d26949e1_d26950e1\">Import using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/cpy</span>\n                     command line switch. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"><kbd class=\"ph userinput\"> /cpy /sup xml: </kbd></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>, where <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var> is the name\n                        of the file containing the new language setup.</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"bkp1665702824339__li_d13727e1_d13728e1_d13729e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Compile the language setups using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/mes</span> command line\n                     switch or choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span></span>. </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zum1665703230237.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$LANGUAGE</a><p>Specify the language to use for global objects and language setups.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sdn1665703008210.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$language</a><p>Return or set the current language code used for language-related global objects and language setups.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yfd1665703273621.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/lse</a><p>Copy language setups to an XML file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qcr1665702695577.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/cpy</a><p>Copy one or more entity occurrences from a source database or XML file to another.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ddc1665702657086.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/mes</a><p>Compile global messages, help texts, and language setups.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5826844\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5826844\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Working with Language Setups Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Working with Language Setups Language setups allow you to deploy a Uniface application in different languages. Load source definitions for standard language setups from libmsg.usys.xml , located in the uniface\\misc directory of your installation. Create a Library. Import the libmsg.usys.xml : /cpy d:Uniface\\uniface\\misc\\libmsg.usys.xml Edit the language setups. If you want to define your own language setups, first create a new library or use one you already created for global objects. For more information, see Language Setups . Choose More Editors and then select the one of the language setups: Date-time properties —date and time formats. Editor messages —Uniface text editor messages Button Text —button text in panels, as well as texts for structure editor functions such as Next Occurrence Toggle Symbols —labels for the Character Attributes menu, and check boxes in panels Japanese Eras —Japanese eras based on the reigns of the emperors Select or create the library to contain the language definitions. For more information, see Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects . Select an existing definition or define a new one. For example, to create a French language definition, enter FRA as the Name and click OK . In the resulting dialog, set the properties of the type of language setup. For help on specific properties, press F1 . Apply a language definition by setting the $language ProcScript function or the $LANGUAGE assignment setting to the desired language. Setting $language in ProcScript overrides the $LANGUAGE assignment setting. Setting the application language affects not only the language setups, but also global objects such as menus, glyphs, messages, and help texts. Distribute a language setup: Export the language setup using the /lse command line switch. Import using the /cpy command line switch. /cpy /sup xml: FileName , where FileName is the name of the file containing the new language setup. Compile the language setups using the /mes command line switch or choose File > Compile . Related Links $LANGUAGE Specify the language to use for global objects and language setups. $language Return or set the current language code used for language-related global objects and language setups. /lse Copy language setups to an XML file. /cpy Copy one or more entity occurrences from a source database or XML file to another. /mes Compile global messages, help texts, and language setups. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}